{"nodes": [{"id": "qa_report_enterprise_readiness", "label": "Inline QA Report \u2014 Enterprise Readiness (2026-06-09, verdict: NOT ENTERPRISE READY)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "qa_report_xuploader_delete_deadlock", "label": "Finding: XUploader.delete() Nested Event Loop Deadlock", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": "critical item 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Sync delete() created asyncio.new_event_loop() inside an already-running async engine -> RuntimeError/deadlock. BUILD_PLAN 1.3 later found current code already async \u2014 the QA finding was based on older code; no fix needed."}, {"id": "qa_report_statemanager_thread_safety", "label": "Finding: StateManager Not Thread-Safe", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": "critical item 2", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "mark_video_posted/mark_video_failed/update_platform_health mutate _state without holding _save_lock; concurrent CLI + scheduler + dashboard access can corrupt state. Fix: wrap all mutations in the lock (BUILD_PLAN Phase 2.1)."}, {"id": "qa_report_dashboard_password_plaintext", "label": "Finding: Dashboard Password Stored in Plaintext", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": "critical item 4", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "dashboard_password serialized to YAML in cleartext; fix is bcrypt hash-on-save with verify-on-login (BUILD_PLAN 1.4). CHANGELOG v0.1.0 claims SHA-256 hashing while AGENTS.md claims bcrypt \u2014 docs disagree on the final mechanism."}, {"id": "qa_report_credential_fallback_unencrypted", "label": "Finding: Fallback Credential Storage Unencrypted", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": "critical item 5", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "When the OS keychain is unavailable, credentials fell back to plaintext JSON, contradicting the module docstring. Fix: Fernet encryption with a machine-derived key (.enc files) \u2014 BUILD_PLAN 1.5, now described as shipped behavior in SECURITY.md."}, {"id": "qa_report_missing_dependencies", "label": "Finding: authlib/httpx Missing, ffmpeg-python Abandoned", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": "critical items 6-7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "authlib and httpx were imported by auth_manager.py but undeclared in pyproject.toml (fresh install crashed), and ffmpeg-python (last release 2019, never imported) was declared but dead. Both now appear correctly in NOTICES.md."}, {"id": "qa_report_cli_agent_readiness", "label": "Finding: CLI Agent-Readiness Gaps", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": "CLI agent-readiness section", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "At QA time the CLI lacked --json, --quiet, --dry-run, meaningful exit codes, and TTY detection, blocking AI-agent consumption. BUILD_PLAN Phase 4 added them; README/AGENTS.md now advertise --json everywhere, exit codes 0/1/2/3/4/10, and auto-JSON on non-TTY."}], "edges": [{"source": "qa_report_enterprise_readiness", "target": "qa_report_xuploader_delete_deadlock", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "qa_report_enterprise_readiness", "target": "qa_report_statemanager_thread_safety", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "QA_REPORT.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 